    "attributes": {
        "action": "Change existing copyright law to explicitly allow for the ripping of CDs",
        "additional_details": "We've removed old and out of use laws such as blasphemy and this should follow suit.\r\n \r\nMany pieces of software prompt you with a \"rip CD\" button when inserting one and many people already treat it as if it's legal.\r\n \r\n",
        "background": "I think that the majority of UK residents are unaware that its illegal to rip a CD and would rip CDs without knowing its breaking the law. This is currently not the case; legislation to legalise CD ripping was revoked in 2015. ",
